Class Sprite

  • java.lang.Object
    • at.ac.tuwien.ims.towardsthelight.Sprite

  • public class Sprite
extends java.lang.Object
    Stores a Bitmap, possibly with multiple frames, how to animate it and where to draw it.
    Author:
    Thomas Koch, Felix Kugler

              int x,
              int y,
              int frameWidth,
              int frameHeight,
              int totalFrames,
              float frameDisplayDuration)
        Create a new Sprite from a bitmap and frame information.
        Parameters:
        bitmap - The bitmap holding the frames of the Sprite.
        x - X position the Sprite is drawn at.
        y - Y position the Sprite is drawn at.
        frameWidth - Width of an individual frame.
        frameHeight - Height of an individual frame.
        totalFrames - Total number of frames.
        frameDisplayDuration - Seconds each frame is being displayed.
